3. Targeted exploitation — test high-impact vulnerabilities (minimum 60% of iterations)
4. Report findings immediately via create_vulnerability_report
5. Iterate with new insights

IMPORTANT: After breadth-first discovery, you MUST shift into exploitation mode. Continuing to run recon tools past 10% of iterations is a methodology failure.

