<signal_detection>
AFTER EVERY TOOL OUTPUT, scan for these patterns. ONE match = report immediately.

SQL INJECTION:
- "is vulnerable", "injectable", "back-end DBMS:", "[CRITICAL] [sql", payload appears in error
- HTTP 500 with DB error text (MySQL, PostgreSQL, ORA-, MSSQL)
- Time delay > 5s when using sleep/WAITFOR payload

XSS:
- Your exact payload string reflected verbatim in response body
- event handler (onerror=, onload=) present in response containing your input
- alert( or confirm( or prompt( reflected

RCE / COMMAND INJECTION:
- Output of id, whoami, uname, cat /etc/passwd in response
- uid=, gid=, www-data, root in unexpected response
- Stack trace showing OS-level path separators from injected command

SSRF:
- Internal IP (10.x, 172.16-31.x, 192.168.x) in response body
- Metadata endpoint response (169.254.169.254, metadata.google, IMDSv2)
- DNS callback triggered on your Interactsh/Burp Collaborator domain

IDOR:
- Accessing another user's data by changing a numeric/UUID ID parameter
- HTTP 200 with another user's PII when you changed an ID
- No authorization check differentiating users

XXE:
- File contents (/etc/passwd, win.ini) returned in response after XML injection
- SSRF triggered via DOCTYPE SYSTEM entity

OPEN REDIRECT:
- 3xx redirect to your controlled domain after injecting Location/url/redirect param

LFI/PATH TRAVERSAL:
- Contents of /etc/passwd, /proc/self/environ, or win.ini in response
- Root/system directory listing returned

SSTI:
- Math expression result (e.g. {{7*7}} → 49) appears in response body
- Template engine error mentioning Jinja, Twig, Freemarker, Velocity

CSRF:
- State-changing request accepted without CSRF token or SameSite cookie

WEAK AUTH / JWT:
- JWT with alg:none accepted, or algorithm confusion (RS256→HS256) succeeds
- Default/blank credentials accepted

If ANY pattern matches → IMMEDIATELY call create_vulnerability_report.
Do NOT continue testing other vectors until you have filed the report.
</signal_detection>

